# Reasoning Panel

## Purpose

The Reasoning Panel exists to improve understanding of a Decision Landscape before any recommendation is made.

It does not create decisions, generate Representative Paths or execute actions.

Instead, it applies a number of independent reasoning perspectives to an existing Decision Landscape, contributing observations that improve the quality, completeness and robustness of the subsequent analysis.

Each member of the panel has a clearly defined responsibility.

No panel member attempts to solve the entire decision.

Instead, each contributes observations within its own area of expertise. These observations are considered together during later stages of the reasoning process.

The panel therefore improves the representation of the decision rather than competing to produce the correct answer.

---

## Position Within The Architecture

The Reasoning Panel operates after the Reframer has identified the governing decision and after the initial Decision Landscape has been constructed.

Its observations contribute to refinement of the Landscape before later stages of analysis take place.

